## Unit 2 Day 17: 

First, let's explore the lesson in the curriculum. To begin, find your ECS Version 5 curriculum and open to page 96.

<a href="http://www.code.org/ecs#page=96" target="_blank">Access a Digital Copy of the Lesson >></a>

![](https://images.code.org/1c9599846068fdc2b1b085e8f52c12a2-image-1441934518806.54.22 PM.png)

#### Key Concepts

1. Students will learn how to demonstrate a problem as a graph.

1. Students will be able to find the minimal spanning tree of a graph. 

#### Common Difficulties

1. The problem is not about finding a path starting at a certain node but about finding a tree that connects all the nodes with lowest cost.

1. Students often solve the problem without learning the algorithm for solving Minimal Spanning Trees. Makes sure students understand the algorithm. A great resource for this might be the <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1cGO6r4XccHinB1LORkVTzEEE_vehZxqQ72jIip0ZRw4/edit" target="_blank">CSP Lesson on Minimal Spanning Trees</a> .  There are lots of other graphs for them to test out their algorithm on as part of the CSP lesson.

